\title{Tulipa Energy}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{version}{1.0.0}

\meta{description}{TulipaEnergyModel.jl — Julia energy system optimization for investment + operation decisions across electricity, hydrogen, heat, gas. Connects to glass-line RWA via geothermal bore modeling.}

\subtree{
\title{Tulipa Energy Model}
\p{Julia optimization model for energy system investment and operation decisions.}

\subtree{
\title{Why This Matters}
\p{TulipaEnergyModel.jl optimizes across multiple energy sectors — electricity, hydrogen, heat, gas. The glass-line RWA (geothermal bore + fiber + compute at Plurigrid Portal, Portland) produces exactly these revenue streams. Tulipa can model:}

\ul{
\li{\strong{GeoToken (g)}: geothermal electricity generation, dispatch optimization}
\li{\strong{ThermalToken (d)}: direct-use heating, district heating network}
\li{\strong{ComputeToken (c)}: compute powered by geothermal, load scheduling}
\li{\strong{LumenToken (b)}: fiber optic capacity allocation}
\li{\strong{BrineToken (n)}: mineral extraction from geothermal brine}
}

\p{The model determines optimal investment timing (when to drill, when to expand) and operation (how to dispatch across revenue streams each hour).}
}

\subtree{
\title{Installation}
\pre{\startverb
using Pkg
Pkg.add("TulipaEnergyModel")
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Core Concepts}
\subtree{
\title{Assets}
\ul{
\li{\strong{Producer}: geothermal plant, solar array}
\li{\strong{Consumer}: compute load, district heating demand}
\li{\strong{Conversion}: heat → electricity (ORC), electricity → compute}
\li{\strong{Storage}: thermal storage, battery}
\li{\strong{Transport}: transmission lines, heat pipes, fiber}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Optimization}
\ul{
\li{Mixed-integer linear programming (MILP)}
\li{Multi-period (hourly, daily, seasonal)}
\li{Investment + operation co-optimization}
\li{Uses HiGHS solver (open source)}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Usage for Glass-Line Modeling}
\pre{\startverb
using TulipaEnergyModel

# Define the geothermal bore as a Producer asset
# Portland Cascadia volcanic arc: 40-60°C/km gradient
# 2km bore → 80-120°C fluid temperature
# Binary ORC cycle → ~10% thermal-to-electric efficiency

# Model inputs:
# - Drilling cost: $5M-10M per bore
# - Thermal output: ~5 MWth continuous
# - Electric output: ~500 kWe (binary cycle)
# - Revenue: electricity + heat + compute + fiber + brine
# - DOE EGS grant: up to $25M match

# The optimization tells you:
# 1. When to invest (NPV maximizing drill date)
# 2. How to dispatch (hourly revenue allocation)
# 3. Break-even timeline (years to payback)
# 4. Optimal capacity sizing (bore depth, ORC rating)
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Integration with Allocator}
\p{The Move allocator's glass-line strategy (\code{\startverb TRIT_MINUS\stopverb}, conservative/physical) reads its \code{\startverb observed_apy_bps\stopverb} from a Tulipa model run:}

\pre{\startverb
Tulipa model run (offline, Julia)
  → annual revenue estimate ($/yr)
  → convert to APT at current price
  → set as observed_apy_bps in Move strategy
  → allocator rebalance() fold includes physical yield

This bridges continuous (DeFi) and discontinuous (physical) yield.
\stopverb}
}

